A: You are using PrintWriter.write() which writes the string as is. It does not append a newline character. So, when you read the lines using BufferedReader, it reads until it finds a newline character. Since you are not providing a newline character after "1", "2" and "3", it reads them as a single line.

You should use PrintWriter.println() instead of PrintWriter.write() to write a line break.

